안녕하세요! 법무사 시험을 준비하는 꾸준맨 부맨입니다.
이전에는 장교(ROTC 출신)로 해병대에 6년간 몸담았고, 전역 후 그간 배워보고 싶었던 영상 편집, 코딩, IT(네트워크, 정보보안 등) 여러가지를 공부 했습니다. 그러던 중 좋은 기회를 만나 쿠팡 자회사인 CFS에 입사. 물류센터에서 근무를 했습니다. 군인시절부터 조직(회사)에 의지 하지 않아도 되는 내 능력으로 내 삶을 살고 싶다는 생각을 자주 했고, 경제적으로 독립한 전문가(장인)가 되고 싶었습니다. 

군대 후배의 추천으로 법무사에 도전하게 되었고, 쿠팡 퇴사 후 2021년 8월 말부터 법무사 1차 공부를 시작해서, 1년 만에 집에서 인강으로 22년 법무사 1차 시험에 합격하였고, 당해 2차 시험은 130명 안에 들지 못했습니다. 23년에 2차 공부를 후회없이 하였지만 불합격했습니다. 새로운 마음으로 재동차 도전중입니다. 같이 힘내요🔥🔥🔥

22년 11월 2차 시험이 끝나고 공부가 잘 되지 않아, 2023년 새해를 맞아 스터디윗미를 해보자는 생각을 했고, 열심히 실행하고 있습니다. 항상 시작이 가장 어려운 것 같습니다. JUST DO IT!!!그래도 해보는게 중요하다고 생각합니다.

미라클 모닝, 미라클 러닝, 공부, 독서 등 스스로 동기부여하려고 노력하고 있고, 가지고 있는 좋은 에너지들을 많은 분들과 주고 받고 싶어요! 부지러너 여러분들과 같이 2024년 목표 달성 해요! 들어와서 봐주시는 분들 정말 감사합니다!

- have your materials ready to go
- have drinks/food ready so you don't have to get up to go get necessities
- have a clear idea of what you want to accomplish during the session (i.e., choose a task from your to-do list)


✧･ﾟ during the breaks:
- stop working as soon as the timer hits, even if you're mid-sentence
- make sure to get up, do some simple stretches
- refill anything that needs to get refilled
- talk to friends/update family

This 24/7 stream from Studyistic is designed to motivate students anywhere, anytime! The study sessions are broadcast live, this makes it possible to study together at the same time with students from all over the world! You might even meet someone who studies the same as you but is 3000 km away from you. How 🆒 isn't this? Feel free to post a message in the chat and in no time you will have a whole group of study friends with you!😍

📌📌HOW TO USE THIS STREAM?
📖During the study sessions (always 50 minutes), study as hard as you can!🫡 
📢Then in the 10-minute break there is room for relaxation. During the break, there are many students who tell in the chat how their session was, what the plans are for the next session, or just something fun they want to share. Sharing with others in the chat what the plans are for the other sessions can be extra motivating.

S29.title: 勉強動画 毎日24時間・日本初 study with me ポモドーロタイマー🍅 2025-05-13 12:04
S29.description:
この放送は 【１】日本初の勉強動画を24時間毎日放送 【２】YouTubeLiveを活用したオンライン自習室 【３】学習記録機能付きのチャット です。(最新のお知らせ: https://www.notion.so/manten120/1e3702349dcc4cdea53fcfc812d89ff9?pvs=4)

【１】

日本初！24時間毎日、勉強している姿を放送し続けるチャンネルです。

This is Japanese First 24/7/365 study broad cast

生放送と再放送を交互に行い24時間放送しています(2018年8月14日開始)

★10年間、毎日生放送します　※2028年まで。生放送の時間帯は主のライフスタイルの変化に応じて変わります。

★右下のタイマーは

⏰25分勉強(赤)

⏰5分休憩(緑)

を繰り返しています

4回目の休憩は20分です

🍅このタイマーによる勉強法をポモドーロ勉強法といいます🍅

🍅この放送では25分間の勉強を1回することを "1コマ勉強する" と数えています🍅

【２】

日本で初めてYouTubeLiveを活用したオンライン自習室(通称：満点ルーム)です！

配信主Mantenが運営するオンライン自習室(満点ルーム)で視聴者さんどうし一緒に勉強しませんか? 

スマホやウェブカメラで机をうつせば、あなたの部屋が世界中の人と一緒に勉強できる自習室になります。

たまにYouTubeにうつります。

満点ルームの運営管理は全て かずちゃむ (Twitter: https://twitter.com/kazchamu_manten ) ちゃんにお任せしております

満点ルームの使い方  https://manten120.notion.site/c31bd3cef255412da64be11334516d8d?pvs=4

【３】

世界初!! YoutubeLiveのチャットで学習の記録をつけられます！

コマンド(!25など)をチャットに書き込むことで学習記録をつけることができます。

満点学習帳 ( https://www.mantenroom.com ) と連携しています。

くわしくは上記リンクと下の 【コマンドの使い方】 にて。

【コマンドの使い方】

!25 など!で始まる単語をコマンドと言います。コマンドをチャットに書き込むとbot(自動返信ロボット🤖)を通じて学習の記録をつけられます。

!make

あなたの学習記録ページを作成します

学習記録ページはサイト満点学習帳 ( https://www.mantenroom.com )  に作成されます。

!home

あなたの学習記録ページのURLを返します

!25

1回25分の勉強回数(コマ数)を記録します

今日のコマ数と過去全期間の累計コマ数を返します

学習記録ページに反映されます

(!25aと!25bも同じ機能のコマンドです

ほかの人とタイミングがかぶると反応しないので、

かぶりやすいこのコマンドだけ3種類用意してます)

!delete

学習記録ページに関するすべてのデータを削除します😭

そのほか満点学習帳と連携するコマンドの一覧は『学習記録ページ → ? → 目標設定(仮) → ページ最下部』にて見れます。

ここまでのコマンドは主にコマルチャンbotが返信してくれます⛄

コマルチャンbotが担当するのは満点学習帳・学習記録・満点ルームに関するコマンドです。

満点ルームに関するコマンドは

!room

満点ルーム(オンライン自習室)でカメラをつけて利用した時間を表示する。満点ルームを利用していない人が使うと『0時間0分』と返信されます。

🤖🤖🤖🤖🤖

ここから下のコマンドはNight botが返信してくれます。Night botが担当するコマンドは満点学習帳・学習記録には記録されませんが、モチベを高めたるために自由に使ってくださいませ💨

!in

勉強開始の宣言

!out

勉強終了の宣言

!break 10

10分間の休憩と10分後に必ず戻ってくる宣言

数字は自由に変えられます

数字の前に半角スペースが必要です

他にもいろいろなコマンドがあるよ✨

他の人が使っているのを見て少しずつ覚えていこう！

(Night botが担当する全コマンドのリストはありません)

🤖🤖🤖🤖🤖

【その他】

★チャット欄では勉強に関する話題を書き込んで、視聴者さんどうし切磋琢磨しましょう。勉強から著しく逸脱する話題はNGです。

(これは放送主及びモデレーターによるチャット管理の指針です。発言の萎縮につながるため視聴者さんどうしで注意しあうことは極力お控えください) 

★初見さんは「半年ROMる」といいかも

(しばらく読むのだけに専念して、どんな書き込みが歓迎されるか、雰囲気がつかめるまで書き込みを控えること)

★視聴者さん同士の呼び名について

呼び捨ては禁止です。削除します。

「～と呼んでいいですか？」「～と呼んでください」等のコメントは禁止です。

★BGMは集中力を高める雨音です。ピアノサウンドもミックスしてあります。 

★モデレーター(満点モデレーターチーム)

チャットで名前が青くなっている人です。(Botを除く)

不適切発言の削除など、平和なチャットを保つため協力してくださっています

S46.title: 50대 감정평가사 도전기! 12HR-STUDY WITH ME (스터디 윗미)/공무원 시험/수험생/전문직 시험/혼자 공부/캠스터디/Huntington Beach/채팅은 쉬는시간에~ 2025-05-13 12:04
S46.description:
50대에 접어들게 되면서....
감히 감정평가사라는 정말 어려운 시험에 도전하게 되었습니다.
서울대, 연고대 출신 합격생이 가장 많고, 
8천여명중에 150~200여명 안팎의 인원만 합격하는 극악의 난이도의 시험입니다.
50대는 1년에 보통 전국에서 2~3명 내외로 합격하더군요....
그런 똑똑하고 체력좋은 젊은 20대~30대 친구들한테 제가 무모한 싸움을 걸었네요.
몸과 머리가 젊을때 같지않지만, 절실함 하나만을 가지고 시작했습니다!
유튜브 공부법은 약하디 약한 저의 의지를 바로 잡는데 꼭 필요한 장치인것 같습니다.
매일매일 이해하지 못하고 암기하지 못함에서 오는 
'불합격하면 어떡하지??'라는 극악의 불안감이 엄습해오지만...
꼭 이겨내겠습니다!
올해 4월 1차, 내년 7월 2차 시험 합격을 목표로 달려가고 있습니다.
저를 아시던 모르시던 한번씩 들어오셔서
*구독, 좋아요 눌러주시고*
[공부 잘하고 있는지 확인해 주시고] 
[만약 나약한 모습을 보인다면 쓴소리해주세요] 
부탁드립니다!!
마지막으로, 
여기 들어 오시는 모든 분들이 준비하시는 시험에 꼭 합격하시길 기원드립니다.
감사합니다!!

As I entered my 50s...
I dare to take a very difficult exam called a certified public appraiser.
It's an extremely difficult exam that only about 150~200 out of 8,000 passed every year in Korea.
Usually, only two or three people in their 50s pass the test a year...
I started a reckless fight against those smart, energetic young people in their 20s and 30s.
My body and head aren't like when I was young, but I started with only one desperation!
The YouTube study method seems to be a necessary device to strengthen my weak will.
Everyday i'm worried that I might fail the exam, but I'll overcome it!
I am studying hard with the goal of passing the first test in April this year. 
and the second exam (Final) in July next year.
Whether you know me or not, please come in.
*Please press subscribe and like*
And please check if I am studying well.
If I don't study or show a weak mental state, please say something bitter.
Please!
Lastly, I hope this real-time streaming will be of great help to your studies.
Thank you!!

S71.title: Study with me for 5 hours - (🔴 LIVE  | ⏱️ 50/10 timer | No music) 2025-05-13 12:04
S71.description:
Ciao friends! I'm Kevin and here you can see me progress and join me in the deed.

I've always been uncomfortable exposing myself, yet here I am, and you might be asking yourself why in 2021 I started streaming my a-- sitting hours when I could do the same off-camera.

The honest reason is, I've been struggling with procrastination for a long time, and despite I could always achieve the expected results I wanted more and I found my solution in the Hawthorne effect, basically "if you are watched, your behavior changes in response to being observed" thus making you more productive and performant.

POOF! The procrastination curse was broken. I was - magically? - able to put in hours of focus on a certain activity without following any butterfly in the process, without any distraction from my mind.
If you want to try the Hawthorne effect on you as I did, you can tell me in chat and join me on Discord (so you can go live with me): https://discord.gg/VPnEJd6PWA.

Not only I could now focus, but I'd also gained confidence in exposing myself in the social field, meeting many wonderful people with whom we shared and keep sharing thoughts and personal events, and laugh together, and whom I can for real call friends.
A *BIG* heartfelt THANK goes to YOU ❤️, as without a viewer there would be no Hawthorne effect and no friends to chat with - there would be no progress.


How do "study with me lives" work?
There are 50/10 Pomodoro timers, where each session is made of 50 minutes of studying/working (progress time) and 10 minutes of chatting/moving (break time).

What are you working on?
I'm either studying medicine or coding.

Do you like pineapple pizza?
No.

Have you even ever tried it?
A fruit on a pizza is wrong. If you want pineapple on something get a damn fruit salad.

Jai Hind everyone!

Join us on this journey to study 6 hours every day! I'm Diksha, currently preparing for the UPSC and other law exams, while also working in the legal field. I do live study sessions following a 50/10 Pomodoro technique and share my day highlights through shorts .
After graduating in 2024, I realized how challenging it can be to study alone, especially for people like me (Library person). This led me to come up with the idea for this channel. I often found myself torn between spending time with friends and staying productive. So, now, I'm working on building a community where we can all spend our time productively.

LIVE TIMINGS:

S95.description:
Board exam is nearing so this is your daily dose of motivation to study. Let's kill procastination and study together

This is the study with me session and here we use the pomodoro technique for studying. Pomodoro technique is one of the most effective studying technique which helps you to boost your focus and productivity while studying. Here we apply the 60/10 format (60 minutes study and 10 minutes break). During break time feel free to chitchat with me in live chat. 

Don't forget to keep water bottle by your side and stay hydrated!



📌Basic information:

: rahulenter22@gmail.com





💭Thoughts and purpose of this channel:

In today's world it's so difficult to congregate your focus for a particular work. There are distractions everywhere and it's too easy to lose your self-consciousness to these distractions. During this period of engrossment, It becomes essential for us to take back our consciousness and get out of the pool of distractions which seems pleasureful to swim in but is slowly submerging us into it. Best way to avoid these things is to be conscious and engage yourself in the activity which is actually important to you. It is the exact purpose of this channel. This channel is rooted onto the foundation of making progress and helping other to make progress. 

Personally, I get motivated by watching other people study. I've been watching these "study with me" sessions of other youtubers from long ago (until I started my own), and being honest, it helped me a lot. I am heartily thankful for those youtubers who helped me to make my study effective and I can confront that they created a positive impact in my life. Since I'm in their place right now, I can't be more happier than to be able to make the same positive impact on other people's life. There is a quotation saying "Helping others is the way we help ourselves". I feel that helping people and being able to make a positive impact in other people's life is the greatest thing a human can do. So, I think that you have understood the soul purpose of creating this channel.

Also, not to forget that this channel is highly inspired by 'James Scholz' who is the original founder and god of 'Study with me' videos. 'Pascal Zoels', '7viksthan' are other popular YouTubers who post similar contents (ps. they are my favorite)
